13
00:01:00,740 --> 00:01:05,670
Let's explore how
the Diffie-Hellman protocol works.

14
00:01:05,670 --> 00:01:10,732
Suppose that Alice and Bob don't know
each other and they would like to share

15
00:01:10,732 --> 00:01:16,363
an encryption key of a symmetric cipher in
order to initiate secure communication.

16
00:01:19,274 --> 00:01:24,823
To do this, first, Alice and
Bob have to agree on two numbers,

17
00:01:24,823 --> 00:01:28,281
a sufficiently large prime number p and

18
00:01:28,281 --> 00:01:33,230
a base generator g,
which is a primitive root modulo P.

19
00:01:35,310 --> 00:01:39,420
Alice chooses a secret number or key a and

20
00:01:39,420 --> 00:01:43,450
computes her public result, capital A,

21
00:01:43,450 --> 00:01:48,660
as g to the power of a mod p and
sends it to Bob.

22
00:01:50,580 --> 00:01:54,930
Bob also chooses a secret number or
key b and

23
00:01:54,930 --> 00:01:59,780
computes his public results,
capital B, as g

24
00:01:59,780 --> 00:02:04,540
to the power of b mod P and
sends it to Alice.

25
00:02:06,720 --> 00:02:11,120
At this point,
a potential attacker may intercept

26
00:02:11,120 --> 00:02:15,190
their communication and
get the public results A and B.

27
00:02:16,430 --> 00:02:21,572
He might also capture p and g when Alice
and Bob are agreeing on these numbers.

28
00:02:21,572 --> 00:02:26,715
Now, Alice computes a shared secret S1

29
00:02:26,715 --> 00:02:32,620
with her secret key a as B
to the power of a mod p.

30
00:02:33,620 --> 00:02:38,150
And, likewise,
Bob computes a shared secret S2 with

31
00:02:38,150 --> 00:02:43,090
his secret key b as A to
the power of b mod p.

32
00:02:44,970 --> 00:02:50,779
It can be mathematically proven that
S1 and S2 actually have the same value.

33
00:02:52,370 --> 00:02:56,810
This shared number is Alice's and
Bob's shared secret and

34
00:02:56,810 --> 00:03:00,907
can be used as an encryption
key of a symmetric cipher.

35
00:03:02,964 --> 00:03:07,437
Because the attacker doesn't
know the secret keys a and b,

36
00:03:07,437 --> 00:03:11,116
he will not be able to
compute the shared secret.

37
